      <h1>Statue of Unity</h1>
    </div>
    <div class="info-content">
      <p>
        The Statue of Unity is a colossal statue of Indian political leader Vallabhbhai Patel, who was a key figure in the country's struggle for independence. It is located in the Indian state of Gujarat, near the Sardar Sarovar Dam on the Narmada River.
      </p>
      <p>
        Standing at a height of 182 meters (597 feet), the Statue of Unity is the world's tallest statue. It was inaugurated on October 31, 2018, to commemorate the contributions of Vallabhbhai Patel in unifying India.
      </p>
      <p>
        The statue has become a major tourist attraction, drawing visitors from across the country and the world. It is surrounded by a picturesque landscape and offers panoramic views of the surrounding area.
      </p>
      <p>
        For more information, you can visit the official <a href="https://www.soutribhav.org/" target="_blank">Statue of Unity website</a>.
